		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>Sept 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1832</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">By the enclosed letter<lb/> you will find that I have not forgotten you<lb/> as you conjectured in your esteemed favour<lb/> per the <persName>Randolph</persName> record on <date>Friday</date><add>&#63;</add>.  I<lb/> thank you much for your interesting statement<lb/> of the Cholera&#44; and am happy to find<lb/> the disease is taking its exit from your<lb/> fine city.  You conjecture right&#44; that<lb/> it is not properly understood&#8212;we have<lb/> the advantage of the experience of all<lb/> the faculty of the <placeName>North</placeName>&#44; doubtless it will<lb/> pass over our city&#44; altho&#39; we are prepared<lb/> for its reception it will nevertheless be a<lb/> very c<add>&#63;</add> visitor.  I have<lb/> certainly been detained visiting you on<lb/> account of the ravages it produced<lb/> at the <placeName>North</placeName>.  I fear the fall will<lb/> have too far advanced to admit<lb/> of my leaving home for a colder region<lb/> however&#44; I anticipate being with you<lb/> in the early part of the spring&#44; God</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>being willing&#44; but most certain some time<lb/> during the summer.  I was pleased to note<lb/> that you think my friends would be pleased<lb/> to see the <hi rend="underline"><persName>Dator</persName></hi><add>&#63;</add>&#44; I assure you none more<lb/> so than the <persName>Dater</persName> himself to see his friends.<lb/>  I must humble you by presenting my friend<lb/> <persName>Mr. Allen</persName> with the enclosed letter.  Should<lb/> you <add>see</add> any of my friends who shall<lb/> inquire&#44; state my reasons for not<lb/> being in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.  I shall<lb/> be glad to hear from you after<lb/> the holidays&#44; and what assistance<lb/> you had with the prayers on <date>Kippur<lb/> Day</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Again I must conclude<lb/> with the best wishes and regard<lb/> of your friend.</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">Jacob De La Motta</persName></p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		</body>
